<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1436,284,563]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,348,320,347]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Occurrence:</emphasis>
Mediterranean Sea and northeast Atlantic, from the British Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen" box="[1149,1351,321,347]" firstAuthor="Mortensen" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" refId="ref192564" refString="Mortensen, T. (1927 a) Handbook of the echinoderms of the British Isles. Oxford University Press, viii + 471 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6841" type="book" year="1927" yearSuffix="a">Mortensen 1927a</bibRefCitation>
) to the northwest African coasts (
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen" box="[448,637,356,383]" firstAuthor="Mortensen" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="178 - 187" refId="ref192529" refString="Mortensen, T. (1925) Echinodermes du Maroc et De Mauritanie. Bulletin de la Societe des sciences naturelles du Maroc, 5 (4 - 5), 178 - 187." type="journal article" year="1925">Mortensen 1925</bibRefCitation>
), including the Azores (
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[911,1071,356,383]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref185837" refString="Koehler, R. (1909) Echinodermes provenant des campagnes du yacht Princesse-Alice (Asteries, Ophiures, Echinides et Crinoides). Resultats des campagnes scientifiques accomplies sur son yacht par Albert Ier Prince Souverain de Monaco, 34, 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="1909">Koehler 1909</bibRefCitation>
), Canary and 
<collectingCountry box="[1231,1362,356,383]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
archipelagos (
<bibRefCitation author="Agassiz" box="[251,406,392,419]" firstAuthor="Agassiz" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 762" refId="ref170857" refString="Agassiz, A. (1872 - 1874) Revision of the Echini. Illustrated catalogue of the Museum of Comparative Zo ˆ logy at Harvard College, 7 (1 - 4), 1 - 762." type="journal article" year="1872">Agassiz 1872</bibRefCitation>
) and the Josephine, Ampere and Meteor seamounts (
<bibRefCitation author="Mironov" box="[998,1166,392,419]" firstAuthor="Mironov" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="96 - 133" refId="ref191675" refString="Mironov, A. N. (2006) Echinoids from seamounts of the north-eastern Atlantic, onshore / offshore gradients in species distribution. In: Mironov, A. N., Gebruk, A. V. &amp; Southward, A. J. (Eds.), Biogeography of the North Atlantic Seamounts. KMK Scientific Press, Russian Academy of Sciences, P. P. Shirshov Institute of Oceanology, Moscow, pp. 96 - 133." type="book chapter" year="2006">Mironov 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
